import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args){
        String text = "Hello World";
        int key = 3;
        
        String encrypted = encrypt(text, key);
        String decrypted = decrypt(encrypted, key);
        
        System.out.println("Original Text: " + text);
        System.out.println("Encrypted Text: " + encrypted);
        System.out.println("Decrypted Text: " + decrypted);
    }
    
    static String encrypt(String text, int key){
        String result = "";
        for (int i = 0; i < text.length(); i++){
            char c = text.charAt(i);
            if (Character.isLetter(c)) {
                char base = Character.isUpperCase(c) ? 'A' : 'a';
                c = (char)((c - base + key) % 26 + base);
            }
            result = result + c;
        }
        return result;
    }
    
    static String decrypt(String text, int key){
        return encrypt(text, 26 - key);
    }
}

Encryption Algorithm

1. Read the plaintext and the key (shift value).


2. For each letter in the plaintext:

Convert the letter to its alphabet position (0–25).

Add the key and take modulo 26.

Convert back to a letter.



3. Combine all letters to form the ciphertext.



Decryption Algorithm

1. Read the ciphertext and the same key.


2. For each letter:

Convert the letter to alphabet position (0–25).

Subtract the key and take modulo 26.

Convert back to a letter.



3. Output the original plaintext.


